<div class="testimonial">
    <h2>There's nothing I look forward to more than my Sunday mornings</h2>
    <img src="<%= asset_path('students/fsssfzgz-e1474528069550-300x300.png') %>" alt="Hikma Academy Image 1">
    <p>I've attended Hikma Academy for more than a year as a scholarship student and there's nothing I look forward to more than my Sunday mornings. Islamic studies in traditional dugsis have always been cut and dry, but Hikma makes it engaging and helps young girls figure out how to integrate the deen into their lives, not just memorize it. I'm grateful, and may Allah fill this program with nothing but barakah. Ameen.</p>
    <div class="author">Salma Ali</div>
</div>

<div class="testimonial">
    <h2>Amazing, powerful, and very educational</h2>
    <img src="<%= asset_path('students/agraheah-e1474576438815-300x300.png') %>" alt="Hikma Academy Image 2">
    <p>My experience with Hikma academy has been an amazing, powerful, and very educational journey. What I enjoyed the most about this program is the fact each chapter or Surah we learned each week had applied to my daily life, empowered me to learn more about my Deen, and improve my interaction with Allah AllahmduAllah! The pursuit of studying Quran was to find my place within the holy book to be able to connect and increase my understating of the words I was reading so I am able to apply it to my everyday life which this program and the teacher has done phenomenal job! She was always prepared to lecture, empower/wow us, and leave us with more desire to learn more.</p>
    <div class="author">Bahja Mohamud</div>
</div>

<div class="testimonial">
    <h2>That perfect balance</h2>
    <img src="<%= asset_path('students/ifrah-e1474576608225-150x150.jpg') %>" alt="Hikma Academy Image 7">
    <p>Being a part of Hikma Academy has impacted my life immensely Alhamdulilah. I was looking for a Tafseer class that would incorporate a structured class environment along with likeminded sisters who could have a productive discussion and reflect on the subject material. I was overjoyed to find that perfect balance with our instructor Kaltun’s class mashaAllah. Our notes were organized and goal oriented. We also had examinations at the end of every Surah which motivated me even more to study and excel. Overall I would recommend this class to anyone who is aiming to study the tafseer on a more in depth level and participate in reflections that sister Kaltun as well as other sisters have to share masha’Aallah.</p>
    <div class="author">Ifrah Abdi</div>
</div>

<div class="testimonial">
    <h2>Inspirational and thought-provoking</h2>
    <img src="<%= asset_path('students/Sagal-Nur-300x300.png') %>" alt="Hikma Academy Image 4">
    <p>When I first signed up for Hikma Academy’s Tafseer class, I had no expectations. At that time, I didn’t know what I was missing or what I was looking for. The class has not only allowed me to understand the Quran in terms I’ve never understood before but has also given me the chance to connect with my Creator, Alhamdullilah. I felt like the Quran and I noticed one another for the first time! What I value most about this experience is the inspirational and thought-provoking lessons. There’s always a lesson to take home after class. The class started me on a life-long path for seeking Allah and a personal growth which I’ve never known before taking the tafseer class.</p>
    <div class="author">Sagal Nur</div>
</div>

<div class="testimonial">
    <h2>Non-Judgmental Zone</h2>
    <img src="<%= asset_path('students/Osob-Mohamed-300x300.jpeg') %>" alt="Hikma Academy Image 5">
    <p>I signed up for Hikma Academy’s Tafseer class hoping to gain more knowledge and better understanding of the deen in a more comfortable setting where I am not being judged or feel overwhelmed but rather slowly make necessary life changes as learn little by little. What I value most about having been part of the class is the creating of amazing bonds with genuine people who crave to be better and do better together. I value the time spent in the classroom. There is no space in time. I am glued to my seat. I was challenged spiritually. This class increased my iman. I began to implement what I learned outside of the classroom. I grew patient and grateful everyday.</p>
    <div class="author">Osob Mohamed</div>
</div>

<div class="testimonial">
    <h2>Broadened my horizons</h2>
    <img src="<%= asset_path('students/muslimah-silhouette-e1399917788374.jpg') %>" alt="Hikma Academy Image 6">
    <p>Hikma Academy was a beautiful experience that has broadened my horizons. I came knowing I shall expand my knowledge in the tafsir class, but I walked away stronger intellectually. I was not prepared for how the Quran forces you to reflect and interact with it. Allah asks us numerously to think and use our brain. The more I reflected the more I felt grateful, and gained knowledge and understanding; thus loving the class.  I’ve never felt closer to Allah-my maker, provider, sustainer, master- the one who loves me the most and the one who is closest to me. This class has made me cognizant of Allah at all times from suratul Fatiha for understanding Allah to suratul ad-Duhaa for when one is in depression.  Before this class my relationship with Allah was both fear and hope. But after taking this class I now have love for Allah and his beautiful messenger Mohamed (S.A.W).</p>
    <div class="author">Mulki Noor</div>
</div>

<div class="testimonial">
    <h2>In a room full of potentials and hope</h2>
    <img src="<%= asset_path('students/Farhiya-Hassan-e1474576786408-300x300.png') %>" alt="Hikma Academy Image 3">
    <p>My name is Farhiya Hassan and I'm assistant for Ustadha Kaltun Karani here at Hikma Academy. I have been working with her and wonderful bright teen students for a year. I also have been a student taking classes with the adults. Growing up in America and going to Islamic schools or the weekend schools here I understand how most of our students feel. I'm pretty jealous of how they're learning the Quran and the Sunnah. Kaltun's teaching is different than what we are used to. While teaching the Tafseer (translation) of the Quran she combines it with the Seerah (biography) of the Prophet (PBUH). The students are learning to understand their religion better and be proud of it. When the class ends each student is walking out feeling touched and amazed at more than 1 thing that resonated with them. Sunday is the most exciting day of the week because I'm in a room full of potentials and hope. I see our future doctors, lawyers and scholars. I see women that know their religion and can teach it to their families, neighbors, coworkers and colleagues. I see sisterhood, friendships, compassion and love.  I see modesty and honor because we see all of this and more in our teacher Kaltun. You can finish school, be a person who loves the Quran and teaches it, be a wife, daughter and a mother and still have time for fun and friends. Our teachers should model for us so we can follow easily and that's what Hikma Academy offers to be: INSPIRATION while LEARNING.</p>
    <div class="author">Farhiya Hassan</div>
</div>

<div class="testimonial">
    <h2>The Power of Knowledge</h2>
    <img src="<%= asset_path('students/muslimah-silhouette-e1399917788374.jpg') %>" alt="Hikma Academy Image 8">
    <p>
        I signed up for Hikma Academy’s Tafseer class hoping to learn the tafseer of the Quran because I was tired of reading ayats that I did not understand. I always wanted to know the message Allah SWT was communicating through the Quran. I was eager for the message and I truly wanted to connect with Allah. Ramadan is my favorite time of the year, and all I ever wanted to know was the story of the Surah and find tranquility in listening to the surah the Imam was reciting. When the opportunity presented itself, I had to sign up for this class because I believe that it was an answered dua by Allah.
    </p>
    <p>
        What I value the most about this experience is that I have gained knowledge of Allah SWT. I remember the first day of class we covered the tafseer of Ayatul Kursi, and in this ayah (the most powerful ayah in the Quran), Allah SWT introduces himself to the believers. On this day, I was no longer hopeless and I no longer viewed my sins as the very thing that will destroy me but rather a doubt in Allah SWT. This was the beginning of my journey of knowledge and being eager to learn and want more for myself. Every surah is unique on its own and it took me to a whole new world of connecting with Allah and wanting to please Him. Studying the tafseer of the Quran is both a spiritual and personal growth. May Allah swt guide us all and grant us a good ending.
    </p>
    <div class="author">Sagal Muse</div>
</div>

<div class="testimonial">
    <h2>Deeper understanding</h2>
    <img src="<%= asset_path('students/Faduma-Warsame-150x150.png') %>" alt="Hikma Academy Image 16">
    <p>I signed up for Hikma Academy’s Tafseer class hoping for a deeper understanding of the Qur’an and what I value most about this experience is the practical action items gained from each class and the spirit of sisterhood.  This experience has really made me feel more accountable about investing in my spiritual development and doing all that I can to keep the iman in my heart that is flickering on and off every now and then.</p>
